d\Omega = \omega \wedge \Omega
d\Omega
d\Omega = -X^{1}Y^{2}kdx - X^{1}Y^{3}k^{2}xdy - X^{1}Y^{3}k^{2}ydx + X^{2}Y^{1}kdx - 2X^{2}Y^{3}k^{2}xdx + X^{3}Y^{1}k^{2}ydx + X^{3}Y^{1}k^{2}xdy + 2X^{3}Y^{2}k^{2}xdx + X^{3}Y^{4}kdx - X^{4}Y^{3}kdx
X=X^{1}\frac{\partial}{\partial x} + X^{2}\frac{\partial}{\partial y} + X^{3}\frac{\partial}{\partial v} + X^{4}\frac{\partial}{\partial w}
Y=Y^{1}\frac{\partial}{\partial x} + Y^{2}\frac{\partial}{\partial y} + Y^{3}\frac{\partial}{\partial v} + Y^{4}\frac{\partial}{\partial w}
